        <li><strong>Lossless:</strong> WAV</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="spec-card">
      <h4>Quality</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Bitrate:</strong> 192kbps</li>
        <li><strong>Sample Rate:</strong> 44100 Hz</li>
        <li><strong>Channels:</strong> Stereo</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="spec-card">
      <h4>Normalization</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Target:</strong> -14 LUFS</li>
        <li><strong>True Peak:</strong> -1 dB</li>
        <li>Matches streaming platform standards</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="spec-card">
      <h4>Loop Points</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Crossfade:</strong> 50ms</li>
        <li>Ensure seamless loop points</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="accessibility">
  <h2>Audio Accessibility</h2>

  <div class="accessibility-principles">
    <div class="principle">Never make audio the only feedback channel</div>
    <div class="principle">Always pair with visual feedback</div>
    <div class="principle">Provide option to disable all sounds</div>
    <div class="principle">Respect system mute/volume settings</div>
    <div class="principle">Avoid sudden loud sounds</div>
  </div>

  <h3>Screen Reader Considerations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Audio cues should not conflict with screen reader output</li>
    <li>Important state changes should have text alternatives</li>
    <li>Background audio should be pausable</li>
  </ul>
</section>

